import React, {useState} from 'react'
import Nav from 'react-bootstrap/Nav'
import Navbar from 'react-bootstrap/Navbar'
import Container from 'react-bootstrap/Container'
import NavDropdown from 'react-bootstrap/NavDropdown'
function Navigation() {
    return (
        <Navbar bg="light" expand="lg">
            <Container>
                <Nav>
                    <Nav.Link href="#action1">Prices</Nav.Link>
                    <Nav.Link href="#action2">Learn</Nav.Link>
                    <Nav.Link href="#action3">Individuals</Nav.Link>
                    <Nav.Link href="#action4">Creators</Nav.Link>
                    <NavDropdown title="Company" id="navbarScrollingDropdown">
                    <NavDropdown.Item href="#action5">Team</NavDropdown.Item>
                    <NavDropdown.Item href="#action6">Partners</NavDropdown.Item>
                    <NavDropdown.Divider />
                    <NavDropdown.Item href="#action5">Blog</NavDropdown.Item>
                    </NavDropdown>
                </Nav>
                            
                    <Navbar.Toggle aria-controls="navbarScroll" />
                        <Navbar.Collapse id="navbarScroll" className='justify-content-end'>
                            <Nav
                                className="mx-auto"
                                style={{ maxHeight: '100px' }}
                                navbarScroll
                            >
                                <Navbar.Brand className="mx-auto justify-content-center" href="#">NiftyTunes</Navbar.Brand>
                               
                            </Nav>
                            
                            <Nav >
                                <Nav.Link href="#signin"> Sign in</Nav.Link>
                                <Nav.Link href="#getstarted"> Get Started </Nav.Link>
                            </Nav>
      
                        </Navbar.Collapse>
                </Container>
        </Navbar>
    )
}

export default Navigation
